      • checkField

        protected void checkField(IField field)
                   throws IllegalArgumentException
        Description copied from class: RuntimeInstruction
        Check that the given field matches this run time instruction's capabilities. In particular, can we decode this field.

        Base implementation just returns since the base implementation can handle all FAST fields.

        Specialist subclasses should override this method with code that checks the suitability of the given field. For example, a subclass that only knows how to decode int32 values will reject any field which is not int32.

        Overrides:
        checkField in class RuntimeInstruction
        Parameters:
        field - Field to be checked.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if we can't handle (eg decode) this field.

                         throws IOException
        Description copied from class: CopyBase
        Decode the next value from the associated input stream, returning the value in an ITagValue taken from the given msg.

        Note that this will never return an isNone() value - it will always return null instead.
